The paper is about a new distributed training system for deep learning called Stanza, which aims to reduce the data transfer volume between workers and servers in a parameter server architecture. This topic is closely related to several sub-categories in computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), distributed computing (cs.DC), computer vision (cs.CV), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). Among these, machine learning (cs.LG) is the most likely sub-category, as the paper focuses on improving the training efficiency of deep learning models. Distributed computing (cs.DC) and computer vision (cs.CV) are also highly relevant, as they deal with the challenges of distributed training and image processing, respectively. Data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) are less likely but still possible sub-categories, as they involve techniques that can be applied to improve the performance of deep learning systems.
